%% Diagram: Surrogate-key purge propagation across a global PoP fleet (Fastly-style bimodal multicast)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as Origin app
    participant API as Purge API\n(any PoP)
    participant PoP1 as Ingress PoP
    participant Peers as Other PoPs\n(global fleet)
    participant Cache as Cache servers\nin each PoP
    participant User

    App->>API: POST /purge\nSurrogate-Key: product-123
    Note over API: Validate auth, expand key
    API->>PoP1: Accept purge (≈ 5 ms)
    PoP1-)Peers: UDP broadcast\n(double-delivered to ≥2 nodes/PoP)
    Peers-)Peers: Gossip / anti-entropy\n(repair lost packets)
    Note over Peers,Cache: No ACKs — latency bounded by\nspeed-of-light transit, not RTT round-trips
    Peers->>Cache: Mark matching objects stale\n(soft) or evict (hard)
    Note over Cache: Median global propagation ≈ 150 ms

    User->>Cache: GET /product/123
    alt Soft purge
        Cache-->>User: Stale 200 (revalidate in background)
    else Hard purge
        Cache->>App: Conditional GET / origin fetch
        App-->>Cache: 200 fresh
        Cache-->>User: 200 fresh
    end
